    "swedishParallel": "Swedish has 'han/hon/den/det' for he/she/it. Greek uses αυτός/αυτή/αυτό. The good news: είναι is ONE form for he, she, AND it — just like Swedish 'är'. You only need to change the pronoun, not the verb!"
